The article discusses the tragic mass shooting that took place in an elementary school in Uvalde, Texas, one year ago. Nineteen children and two educators lost their lives in the shooting. The article highlights the ongoing issue of gun violence in the United States, particularly its impact on children. It mentions that gun violence remains the leading cause of death for children in the country and that one in five Americans has lost a family member to gun violence. The families affected by the Uvalde shooting have turned their grief into advocacy for gun safety measures. The article acknowledges President Biden's efforts in signing significant gun safety legislation and implementing executive actions but emphasizes that more needs to be done. The author calls on leaders in Congress and state legislatures to take action to address gun violence.